20constexpr const ImmutableString kSpecifiedMultipleTimes(" specified multiple times");
21constexpr const ImmutableString kInvariantMultipleTimes(
22 "The invariant qualifier specified multiple times.");
23constexpr const ImmutableString kPreciseMultipleTimes(
24 "The precise qualifier specified multiple times.");
25constexpr const ImmutableString kPrecisionMultipleTimes(
26 "The precision qualifier specified multiple times.");
27constexpr const ImmutableString kLayoutMultipleTimes(
28 "The layout qualifier specified multiple times.");
29constexpr const ImmutableString kLayoutAndInvariantDisallowed(
30 "The layout qualifier and invariant qualifier cannot coexist in the same "
31 "declaration according to the grammar.");
32constexpr const ImmutableString kInterpolationMultipleTimes(
33 "The interpolation qualifier specified multiple times.");
34constexpr const ImmutableString kOutputLayoutMultipleTimes(
35 "Output layout location specified multiple times.");
36constexpr const ImmutableString kInvariantQualifierFirst(
37 "The invariant qualifier has to be first in the expression.");
38constexpr const ImmutableString kStorageAfterInterpolation(
39 "Storage qualifiers have to be after interpolation qualifiers.");
40constexpr const ImmutableString kPrecisionAfterInterpolation(
41 "Precision qualifiers have to be after interpolation qualifiers.");
42constexpr const ImmutableString kStorageAfterLayout(
43 "Storage qualifiers have to be after layout qualifiers.");
44constexpr const ImmutableString kPrecisionAfterLayout(
45 "Precision qualifiers have to be after layout qualifiers.");
46constexpr const ImmutableString kPrecisionAfterStorage(
47 "Precision qualifiers have to be after storage qualifiers.");
48constexpr const ImmutableString kPrecisionAfterMemory(
49 "Precision qualifiers have to be after memory qualifiers.");
50
51// GLSL ES 3.10 does not impose a strict order on type qualifiers and allows multiple layout
52// declarations.
53// GLSL ES 3.10 Revision 4, 4.10 Order of Qualification
54bool AreTypeQualifierChecksRelaxed(int shaderVersion)
55{
56 return shaderVersion >= 310;
57}
58
59bool IsScopeQualifier(TQualifier qualifier)
60{
61 return qualifier == EvqGlobal || qualifier == EvqTemporary;
62}
63
64bool IsScopeQualifierWrapper(const TQualifierWrapperBase *qualifier)
65{
66 if (qualifier->getType() != QtStorage)
67 return false;
68 const TStorageQualifierWrapper *storageQualifier =
69 static_cast<const TStorageQualifierWrapper *>(qualifier);
70 TQualifier q = storageQualifier->getQualifier();
71 return IsScopeQualifier(q);
72}
73
74// Returns true if the invariant/precise for the qualifier sequence holds
75bool IsInvariantCorrect(const TTypeQualifierBuilder::QualifierSequence &qualifiers)
76{
77 // We should have at least one qualifier.
78 // The first qualifier always tells the scope.
79 return qualifiers.size() >= 1 && IsScopeQualifierWrapper(qualifiers[0]);
80}
81
82ImmutableString QualifierSpecifiedMultipleTimesErrorMessage(const ImmutableString &qualifierString)
83{
84 ImmutableStringBuilder errorMsg(qualifierString.length() + kSpecifiedMultipleTimes.length());
85 errorMsg << qualifierString << kSpecifiedMultipleTimes;
86 return errorMsg;
87}
88
89// Returns true if there are qualifiers which have been specified multiple times
90// If areQualifierChecksRelaxed is set to true, then layout qualifier repetition is allowed.
91bool HasRepeatingQualifiers(const TTypeQualifierBuilder::QualifierSequence &qualifiers,
92 bool areQualifierChecksRelaxed,
93 ImmutableString *errorMessage)
94{
95 bool invariantFound = false;
96 bool preciseFound = false;
97 bool precisionFound = false;
98 bool layoutFound = false;
99 bool interpolationFound = false;
100
101 unsigned int locationsSpecified = 0;
102 bool isOut = false;
103
104 // The iteration starts from one since the first qualifier only reveals the scope of the
105 // expression. It is inserted first whenever the sequence gets created.
106 for (size_t i = 1; i < qualifiers.size(); ++i)
107 {
108 switch (qualifiers[i]->getType())
109 {
110 case QtInvariant:
111 {
112 if (invariantFound)
113 {
114 *errorMessage = kInvariantMultipleTimes;
115 return true;
116 }
117 invariantFound = true;
118 break;
119 }
120 case QtPrecise:
121 {
122 if (preciseFound)
123 {
124 *errorMessage = kPreciseMultipleTimes;
125 return true;
126 }
127 preciseFound = true;
128 break;
129 }
130 case QtPrecision:
131 {
132 if (precisionFound)
133 {
134 *errorMessage = kPrecisionMultipleTimes;
135 return true;
136 }
137 precisionFound = true;
138 break;
139 }
140 case QtLayout:
141 {
142 if (layoutFound && !areQualifierChecksRelaxed)
143 {
144 *errorMessage = kLayoutMultipleTimes;
145 return true;
146 }
147 if (invariantFound && !areQualifierChecksRelaxed)
148 {
149 // This combination is not correct according to the syntax specified in the
150 // formal grammar in the ESSL 3.00 spec. In ESSL 3.10 the grammar does not have
151 // a similar restriction.
152 *errorMessage = kLayoutAndInvariantDisallowed;
153 return true;
154 }
155 layoutFound = true;
156 const TLayoutQualifier &currentQualifier =
157 static_cast<const TLayoutQualifierWrapper *>(qualifiers[i])->getQualifier();
158 locationsSpecified += currentQualifier.locationsSpecified;
159 break;
160 }
161 case QtInterpolation:
162 {
163 // 'centroid' is treated as a storage qualifier
164 // 'flat centroid' will be squashed to 'flat'
165 // 'smooth centroid' will be squashed to 'centroid'
166 if (interpolationFound)
167 {
168 *errorMessage = kInterpolationMultipleTimes;
169 return true;
170 }
171 interpolationFound = true;
172 break;
173 }
174 case QtStorage:
175 {
176 // Go over all of the storage qualifiers up until the current one and check for
177 // repetitions.
178 TQualifier currentQualifier =
179 static_cast<const TStorageQualifierWrapper *>(qualifiers[i])->getQualifier();
180 if (currentQualifier == EvqVertexOut || currentQualifier == EvqFragmentOut)
181 {
182 isOut = true;
183 }
184 for (size_t j = 1; j < i; ++j)
185 {
186 if (qualifiers[j]->getType() == QtStorage)
187 {
188 const TStorageQualifierWrapper *previousQualifierWrapper =
189 static_cast<const TStorageQualifierWrapper *>(qualifiers[j]);
190 TQualifier previousQualifier = previousQualifierWrapper->getQualifier();
191 if (currentQualifier == previousQualifier)
192 {
193 *errorMessage = QualifierSpecifiedMultipleTimesErrorMessage(
194 previousQualifierWrapper->getQualifierString());
195 return true;
196 }
197 }
198 }
199 break;
200 }
201 case QtMemory:
202 {
203 // Go over all of the memory qualifiers up until the current one and check for
204 // repetitions.
205 // Having both readonly and writeonly in a sequence is valid.
206 // GLSL ES 3.10 Revision 4, 4.9 Memory Access Qualifiers
207 TQualifier currentQualifier =
208 static_cast<const TMemoryQualifierWrapper *>(qualifiers[i])->getQualifier();
209 for (size_t j = 1; j < i; ++j)
210 {
211 if (qualifiers[j]->getType() == QtMemory)
212 {
213 const TMemoryQualifierWrapper *previousQualifierWrapper =
214 static_cast<const TMemoryQualifierWrapper *>(qualifiers[j]);
215 TQualifier previousQualifier = previousQualifierWrapper->getQualifier();
216 if (currentQualifier == previousQualifier)
217 {
218 *errorMessage = QualifierSpecifiedMultipleTimesErrorMessage(
219 previousQualifierWrapper->getQualifierString());
220 return true;
221 }
222 }
223 }
224 break;
225 }
226 default:
227 UNREACHABLE();
228 }
229 }
230
231 if (locationsSpecified > 1 && isOut)
232 {
233 // GLSL ES 3.00.6 section 4.3.8.2 Output Layout Qualifiers
234 // GLSL ES 3.10 section 4.4.2 Output Layout Qualifiers
235 // "The qualifier may appear at most once within a declaration."
236 *errorMessage = kOutputLayoutMultipleTimes;
237 return true;
238 }
239
240 return false;
241}
242
243// GLSL ES 3.00_6, 4.7 Order of Qualification
244// The correct order of qualifiers is:
245// invariant-qualifier interpolation-qualifier storage-qualifier precision-qualifier
246// layout-qualifier has to be before storage-qualifier.
247//
248// GLSL ES 3.1 relaxes the order of qualification:
249// When multiple qualifiers are present in a declaration, they may appear in any order, but they
250// must all appear before the type.
251bool AreQualifiersInOrder(const TTypeQualifierBuilder::QualifierSequence &qualifiers,
252 int shaderVersion,
253 ImmutableString *errorMessage)
254{
255 if (shaderVersion >= 310)
256 {
257 return true;
258 }
259
260 bool foundInterpolation = false;
261 bool foundStorage = false;
262 bool foundPrecision = false;
263 for (size_t i = 1; i < qualifiers.size(); ++i)
264 {
265 switch (qualifiers[i]->getType())
266 {
267 case QtInvariant:
268 if (foundInterpolation || foundStorage || foundPrecision)
269 {
270 *errorMessage = kInvariantQualifierFirst;
271 return false;
272 }
273 break;
274 case QtInterpolation:
275 if (foundStorage)
276 {
277 *errorMessage = kStorageAfterInterpolation;
278 return false;
279 }
280 else if (foundPrecision)
281 {
282 *errorMessage = kPrecisionAfterInterpolation;
283 return false;
284 }
285 foundInterpolation = true;
286 break;
287 case QtLayout:
288 if (foundStorage)
289 {
290 *errorMessage = kStorageAfterLayout;
291 return false;
292 }
293 else if (foundPrecision)
294 {
295 *errorMessage = kPrecisionAfterLayout;
296 return false;
297 }
298 break;
299 case QtStorage:
300 if (foundPrecision)
301 {
302 *errorMessage = kPrecisionAfterStorage;
303 return false;
304 }
305 foundStorage = true;
306 break;
307 case QtMemory:
308 if (foundPrecision)
309 {
310 *errorMessage = kPrecisionAfterMemory;
311 return false;
312 }
313 break;
314 case QtPrecision:
315 foundPrecision = true;
316 break;
317 case QtPrecise:
318 // This keyword is available in ES3.1 (with extension) or in ES3.2, but the function
319 // should early-out in such a case as the spec doesn't require a particular order to
320 // the qualifiers.
321 UNREACHABLE();
322 break;
323 default:
324 UNREACHABLE();
325 }
326 }
327 return true;
328}
329
330struct QualifierComparator
331{
332 bool operator()(const TQualifierWrapperBase *q1, const TQualifierWrapperBase *q2)
333 {
334 return q1->getRank() < q2->getRank();
335 }
336};
337
338void SortSequence(TTypeQualifierBuilder::QualifierSequence &qualifiers)
339{
340 // We need a stable sorting algorithm since the order of layout-qualifier declarations matter.
341 // The sorting starts from index 1, instead of 0, since the element at index 0 tells the scope
342 // and we always want it to be first.
343 std::stable_sort(qualifiers.begin() + 1, qualifiers.end(), QualifierComparator());
344}
345
346// Handles the joining of storage qualifiers for variables.
347bool JoinVariableStorageQualifier(TQualifier *joinedQualifier, TQualifier storageQualifier)
348{
349 switch (*joinedQualifier)
350 {
351 case EvqGlobal:
352 *joinedQualifier = storageQualifier;
353 break;
354 case EvqTemporary:
355 {
356 switch (storageQualifier)
357 {
358 case EvqConst:
359 *joinedQualifier = storageQualifier;
360 break;
361 default:
362 return false;
363 }
364 break;
365 }
366 case EvqSmooth:
367 {
368 switch (storageQualifier)
369 {
370 case EvqCentroid:
371 *joinedQualifier = EvqCentroid;
372 break;
373 case EvqVertexOut:
374 case EvqGeometryOut:
375 *joinedQualifier = EvqSmoothOut;
376 break;
377 case EvqFragmentIn:
378 case EvqGeometryIn:
379 *joinedQualifier = EvqSmoothIn;
380 break;
381 default:
382 return false;
383 }
384 break;
385 }
386 case EvqFlat:
387 {
388 switch (storageQualifier)
389 {
390 case EvqCentroid:
391 *joinedQualifier = EvqFlat;
392 break;
393 case EvqVertexOut:
394 case EvqGeometryOut:
395 *joinedQualifier = EvqFlatOut;
396 break;
397 case EvqFragmentIn:
398 case EvqGeometryIn:
399 *joinedQualifier = EvqFlatIn;
400 break;
401 default:
402 return false;
403 }
404 break;
405 }
406 case EvqNoPerspective:
407 {
408 switch (storageQualifier)
409 {
410 case EvqCentroid:
411 *joinedQualifier = EvqNoPerspective;
412 break;
413 case EvqVertexOut:
414 case EvqGeometryOut:
415 *joinedQualifier = EvqNoPerspectiveOut;
416 break;
417 case EvqFragmentIn:
418 case EvqGeometryIn:
419 *joinedQualifier = EvqNoPerspectiveIn;
420 break;
421 default:
422 return false;
423 }
424 break;
425 }
426 case EvqCentroid:
427 {
428 switch (storageQualifier)
429 {
430 case EvqVertexOut:
431 case EvqGeometryOut:
432 *joinedQualifier = EvqCentroidOut;
433 break;
434 case EvqFragmentIn:
435 case EvqGeometryIn:
436 *joinedQualifier = EvqCentroidIn;
437 break;
438 default:
439 return false;
440 }
441 break;
442 }
443 case EvqSample:
444 {
445 switch (storageQualifier)
446 {
447 case EvqVertexOut:
448 case EvqGeometryOut:
449 *joinedQualifier = EvqSampleOut;
450 break;
451 case EvqFragmentIn:
452 case EvqGeometryIn:
453 *joinedQualifier = EvqSampleIn;
454 break;
455 default:
456 return false;
457 }
458 break;
459 }
460 default:
461 return false;
462 }
463 return true;
464}
465
466// Handles the joining of storage qualifiers for a parameter in a function.
467bool JoinParameterStorageQualifier(TQualifier *joinedQualifier, TQualifier storageQualifier)
468{
469 switch (*joinedQualifier)
470 {
471 case EvqTemporary:
472 *joinedQualifier = storageQualifier;
473 break;
474 case EvqConst:
475 {
476 switch (storageQualifier)
477 {
478 case EvqIn:
479 *joinedQualifier = EvqConstReadOnly;
480 break;
481 default:
482 return false;
483 }
484 break;
485 }
486 default:
487 return false;
488 }
489 return true;
490}
491
492bool JoinMemoryQualifier(TMemoryQualifier *joinedMemoryQualifier, TQualifier memoryQualifier)
493{
494 switch (memoryQualifier)
495 {
496 case EvqReadOnly:
497 joinedMemoryQualifier->readonly = true;
498 break;
499 case EvqWriteOnly:
500 joinedMemoryQualifier->writeonly = true;
501 break;
502 case EvqCoherent:
503 joinedMemoryQualifier->coherent = true;
504 break;
505 case EvqRestrict:
506 joinedMemoryQualifier->restrictQualifier = true;
507 break;
508 case EvqVolatile:
509 // Variables having the volatile qualifier are automatcally treated as coherent as well.
510 // GLSL ES 3.10, Revision 4, 4.9 Memory Access Qualifiers
511 joinedMemoryQualifier->volatileQualifier = true;
512 joinedMemoryQualifier->coherent = true;
513 break;
514 default:
515 UNREACHABLE();
516 }
517 return true;
518}

520TTypeQualifier GetVariableTypeQualifierFromSortedSequence(
521 const TTypeQualifierBuilder::QualifierSequence &sortedSequence,
522 TDiagnostics *diagnostics)
523{
524 TTypeQualifier typeQualifier(
525 static_cast<const TStorageQualifierWrapper *>(sortedSequence[0])->getQualifier(),
526 sortedSequence[0]->getLine());
527 for (size_t i = 1; i < sortedSequence.size(); ++i)
528 {
529 const TQualifierWrapperBase *qualifier = sortedSequence[i];
530 bool isQualifierValid = false;
531 switch (qualifier->getType())
532 {
533 case QtInvariant:
534 isQualifierValid = true;
535 typeQualifier.invariant = true;
536 break;
537 case QtPrecise:
538 isQualifierValid = true;
539 typeQualifier.precise = true;
540 break;
541 case QtInterpolation:
542 {
543 switch (typeQualifier.qualifier)
544 {
545 case EvqGlobal:
546 isQualifierValid = true;
547 typeQualifier.qualifier =
548 static_cast<const TInterpolationQualifierWrapper *>(qualifier)
549 ->getQualifier();
550 break;
551 default:
552 isQualifierValid = false;
553 }
554 break;
555 }
556 case QtLayout:
557 {
558 const TLayoutQualifierWrapper *layoutQualifierWrapper =
559 static_cast<const TLayoutQualifierWrapper *>(qualifier);
560 isQualifierValid = true;
561 typeQualifier.layoutQualifier = sh::JoinLayoutQualifiers(
562 typeQualifier.layoutQualifier, layoutQualifierWrapper->getQualifier(),
563 layoutQualifierWrapper->getLine(), diagnostics);
564 break;
565 }
566 case QtStorage:
567 isQualifierValid = JoinVariableStorageQualifier(
568 &typeQualifier.qualifier,
569 static_cast<const TStorageQualifierWrapper *>(qualifier)->getQualifier());
570 break;
571 case QtPrecision:
572 isQualifierValid = true;
573 typeQualifier.precision =
574 static_cast<const TPrecisionQualifierWrapper *>(qualifier)->getQualifier();
575 ASSERT(typeQualifier.precision != EbpUndefined);
576 break;
577 case QtMemory:
578 isQualifierValid = JoinMemoryQualifier(
579 &typeQualifier.memoryQualifier,
580 static_cast<const TMemoryQualifierWrapper *>(qualifier)->getQualifier());
581 break;
582 default:
583 UNREACHABLE();
584 }
585 if (!isQualifierValid)
586 {
587 const ImmutableString &qualifierString = qualifier->getQualifierString();
588 diagnostics->error(qualifier->getLine(), "invalid qualifier combination",
589 qualifierString.data());
590 break;
591 }
592 }
593 return typeQualifier;
594}
595
596TTypeQualifier GetParameterTypeQualifierFromSortedSequence(
597 const TTypeQualifierBuilder::QualifierSequence &sortedSequence,
598 TDiagnostics *diagnostics)
599{
600 TTypeQualifier typeQualifier(EvqTemporary, sortedSequence[0]->getLine());
601 for (size_t i = 1; i < sortedSequence.size(); ++i)
602 {
603 const TQualifierWrapperBase *qualifier = sortedSequence[i];
604 bool isQualifierValid = false;
605 switch (qualifier->getType())
606 {
607 case QtInvariant:
608 case QtPrecise:
609 case QtInterpolation:
610 case QtLayout:
611 break;
612 case QtMemory:
613 isQualifierValid = JoinMemoryQualifier(
614 &typeQualifier.memoryQualifier,
615 static_cast<const TMemoryQualifierWrapper *>(qualifier)->getQualifier());
616 break;
617 case QtStorage:
618 isQualifierValid = JoinParameterStorageQualifier(
619 &typeQualifier.qualifier,
620 static_cast<const TStorageQualifierWrapper *>(qualifier)->getQualifier());
621 break;
622 case QtPrecision:
623 isQualifierValid = true;
624 typeQualifier.precision =
625 static_cast<const TPrecisionQualifierWrapper *>(qualifier)->getQualifier();
626 ASSERT(typeQualifier.precision != EbpUndefined);
627 break;
628 default:
629 UNREACHABLE();
630 }
631 if (!isQualifierValid)
632 {
633 const ImmutableString &qualifierString = qualifier->getQualifierString();
634 diagnostics->error(qualifier->getLine(), "invalid parameter qualifier",
635 qualifierString.data());
636 break;
637 }
638 }
639
640 switch (typeQualifier.qualifier)
641 {
642 case EvqIn:
643 case EvqConstReadOnly: // const in
644 case EvqOut:
645 case EvqInOut:
646 break;
647 case EvqConst:
648 typeQualifier.qualifier = EvqConstReadOnly;
649 break;
650 case EvqTemporary:
651 // no qualifier has been specified, set it to EvqIn which is the default
652 typeQualifier.qualifier = EvqIn;
653 break;
654 default:
655 diagnostics->error(sortedSequence[0]->getLine(), "Invalid parameter qualifier ",
656 getQualifierString(typeQualifier.qualifier));
657 }
658 return typeQualifier;
659}
660} // namespace
661
662TLayoutQualifier JoinLayoutQualifiers(TLayoutQualifier leftQualifier,
663 TLayoutQualifier rightQualifier,
664 const TSourceLoc &rightQualifierLocation,
665 TDiagnostics *diagnostics)
666{
667 TLayoutQualifier joinedQualifier = leftQualifier;
668
669 if (rightQualifier.location != -1)
670 {
671 joinedQualifier.location = rightQualifier.location;
672 ++joinedQualifier.locationsSpecified;
673 }
674 if (rightQualifier.yuv != false)
675 {
676 joinedQualifier.yuv = rightQualifier.yuv;
677 }
678 if (rightQualifier.earlyFragmentTests != false)
679 {
680 joinedQualifier.earlyFragmentTests = rightQualifier.earlyFragmentTests;
681 }
682 if (rightQualifier.binding != -1)
683 {
684 joinedQualifier.binding = rightQualifier.binding;
685 }
686 if (rightQualifier.offset != -1)
687 {
688 joinedQualifier.offset = rightQualifier.offset;
689 }
690 if (rightQualifier.matrixPacking != EmpUnspecified)
691 {
692 joinedQualifier.matrixPacking = rightQualifier.matrixPacking;
693 }
694 if (rightQualifier.blockStorage != EbsUnspecified)
695 {
696 joinedQualifier.blockStorage = rightQualifier.blockStorage;
697 }
698
699 for (size_t i = 0u; i < rightQualifier.localSize.size(); ++i)
700 {
701 if (rightQualifier.localSize[i] != -1)
702 {
703 if (joinedQualifier.localSize[i] != -1 &&
704 joinedQualifier.localSize[i] != rightQualifier.localSize[i])
705 {
706 diagnostics->error(rightQualifierLocation,
707 "Cannot have multiple different work group size specifiers",
708 getWorkGroupSizeString(i));
709 }
710 joinedQualifier.localSize[i] = rightQualifier.localSize[i];
711 }
712 }
713
714 if (rightQualifier.numViews != -1)
715 {
716 joinedQualifier.numViews = rightQualifier.numViews;
717 }
718
719 if (rightQualifier.imageInternalFormat != EiifUnspecified)
720 {
721 joinedQualifier.imageInternalFormat = rightQualifier.imageInternalFormat;
722 }
723
724 if (rightQualifier.primitiveType != EptUndefined)
725 {
726 if (joinedQualifier.primitiveType != EptUndefined &&
727 joinedQualifier.primitiveType != rightQualifier.primitiveType)
728 {
729 diagnostics->error(rightQualifierLocation,
730 "Cannot have multiple different primitive specifiers",
731 getGeometryShaderPrimitiveTypeString(rightQualifier.primitiveType));
732 }
733 joinedQualifier.primitiveType = rightQualifier.primitiveType;
734 }
735
736 if (rightQualifier.invocations != 0)
737 {
738 if (joinedQualifier.invocations != 0 &&
739 joinedQualifier.invocations != rightQualifier.invocations)
740 {
741 diagnostics->error(rightQualifierLocation,
742 "Cannot have multiple different invocations specifiers",
743 "invocations");
744 }
745 joinedQualifier.invocations = rightQualifier.invocations;
746 }
747
748 if (rightQualifier.maxVertices != -1)
749 {
750 if (joinedQualifier.maxVertices != -1 &&
751 joinedQualifier.maxVertices != rightQualifier.maxVertices)
752 {
753 diagnostics->error(rightQualifierLocation,
754 "Cannot have multiple different max_vertices specifiers",
755 "max_vertices");
756 }
757 joinedQualifier.maxVertices = rightQualifier.maxVertices;
758 }
759
760 if (rightQualifier.index != -1)
761 {
762 if (joinedQualifier.index != -1)
763 {
764 // EXT_blend_func_extended spec: "Each of these qualifiers may appear at most once"
765 diagnostics->error(rightQualifierLocation, "Cannot have multiple index specifiers",
766 "index");
767 }
768 joinedQualifier.index = rightQualifier.index;
769 }
770
771 return joinedQualifier;
772}

774unsigned int TInvariantQualifierWrapper::getRank() const
775{
776 return 0u;
777}
778
779unsigned int TPreciseQualifierWrapper::getRank() const
780{
781 return 1u;
782}
783
784unsigned int TInterpolationQualifierWrapper::getRank() const
785{
786 return 2u;
787}
788
789unsigned int TLayoutQualifierWrapper::getRank() const
790{
791 return 3u;
792}
793
794unsigned int TStorageQualifierWrapper::getRank() const
795{
796 // Force the 'centroid' auxilary storage qualifier to be always first among all storage
797 // qualifiers.
798 if (mStorageQualifier == EvqCentroid)
799 {
800 return 4u;
801 }
802 else
803 {
804 return 5u;
805 }
806}
807
808unsigned int TMemoryQualifierWrapper::getRank() const
809{
810 return 5u;
811}
812
813unsigned int TPrecisionQualifierWrapper::getRank() const
814{
815 return 6u;
816}

818TTypeQualifier::TTypeQualifier(TQualifier scope, const TSourceLoc &loc)
819 : layoutQualifier(TLayoutQualifier::Create()),
820 memoryQualifier(TMemoryQualifier::Create()),
821 precision(EbpUndefined),
822 qualifier(scope),
823 invariant(false),
824 precise(false),
825 line(loc)
826{
827 ASSERT(IsScopeQualifier(qualifier));
828}

830TTypeQualifierBuilder::TTypeQualifierBuilder(const TStorageQualifierWrapper *scope,
831 int shaderVersion)
832 : mShaderVersion(shaderVersion)
833{
834 ASSERT(IsScopeQualifier(scope->getQualifier()));
835 mQualifiers.push_back(scope);
836}
837
838void TTypeQualifierBuilder::appendQualifier(const TQualifierWrapperBase *qualifier)
839{
840 mQualifiers.push_back(qualifier);
841}
842
843bool TTypeQualifierBuilder::checkSequenceIsValid(TDiagnostics *diagnostics) const
844{
845 bool areQualifierChecksRelaxed = AreTypeQualifierChecksRelaxed(mShaderVersion);
846 ImmutableString errorMessage("");
847 if (HasRepeatingQualifiers(mQualifiers, areQualifierChecksRelaxed, &errorMessage))
848 {
849 diagnostics->error(mQualifiers[0]->getLine(), errorMessage.data(), "qualifier sequence");
850 return false;
851 }
852
853 if (!areQualifierChecksRelaxed &&
854 !AreQualifiersInOrder(mQualifiers, mShaderVersion, &errorMessage))
855 {
856 diagnostics->error(mQualifiers[0]->getLine(), errorMessage.data(), "qualifier sequence");
857 return false;
858 }
859
860 return true;
861}
862
863TTypeQualifier TTypeQualifierBuilder::getParameterTypeQualifier(TDiagnostics *diagnostics) const
864{
865 ASSERT(IsInvariantCorrect(mQualifiers));
866 ASSERT(static_cast<const TStorageQualifierWrapper *>(mQualifiers[0])->getQualifier() ==
867 EvqTemporary);
868
869 if (!checkSequenceIsValid(diagnostics))
870 {
871 return TTypeQualifier(EvqTemporary, mQualifiers[0]->getLine());
872 }
873
874 // If the qualifier checks are relaxed, then it is easier to sort the qualifiers so
875 // that the order imposed by the GLSL ES 3.00 spec is kept. Then we can use the same code to
876 // combine the qualifiers.
877 if (AreTypeQualifierChecksRelaxed(mShaderVersion))
878 {
879 // Copy the qualifier sequence so that we can sort them.
880 QualifierSequence sortedQualifierSequence = mQualifiers;
881 SortSequence(sortedQualifierSequence);
882 return GetParameterTypeQualifierFromSortedSequence(sortedQualifierSequence, diagnostics);
883 }
884 return GetParameterTypeQualifierFromSortedSequence(mQualifiers, diagnostics);
885}
886
887TTypeQualifier TTypeQualifierBuilder::getVariableTypeQualifier(TDiagnostics *diagnostics) const
888{
889 ASSERT(IsInvariantCorrect(mQualifiers));
890
891 if (!checkSequenceIsValid(diagnostics))
892 {
893 return TTypeQualifier(
894 static_cast<const TStorageQualifierWrapper *>(mQualifiers[0])->getQualifier(),
895 mQualifiers[0]->getLine());
896 }
897
898 // If the qualifier checks are relaxed, then it is easier to sort the qualifiers so
899 // that the order imposed by the GLSL ES 3.00 spec is kept. Then we can use the same code to
900 // combine the qualifiers.
901 if (AreTypeQualifierChecksRelaxed(mShaderVersion))
902 {
903 // Copy the qualifier sequence so that we can sort them.
904 QualifierSequence sortedQualifierSequence = mQualifiers;
905 SortSequence(sortedQualifierSequence);
906 return GetVariableTypeQualifierFromSortedSequence(sortedQualifierSequence, diagnostics);
907 }
908 return GetVariableTypeQualifierFromSortedSequence(mQualifiers, diagnostics);
909}
